<section class="public-domain"><a id="reuse" name="reuse"></a>
   <h2>Free to Use and Reuse: Arab Americans</h2>
   <p class="public-domain-abstract">
       <p style="color: #fff">Selected images represent the historical experiences and achievements of Arab Americans, primarily during the early 1900s when many people immigrated from Lebanon and the region known as Syria. A formal celebration of Arab American heritage occurs each year in the United States in April. Unless otherwise noted, the images are from the Prints & Photographs Division.</p> <p style="color: #fff">Browse more <a href="/free-to-use/" style="color: #fff;text-decoration: underline">content that is free to use and reuse <i class="icon icon-angle-double-right"></i></a></p>

   </p>
   <ul class="search-results grid-view public-domain-results">
       
       <li 
           id="featured_public_domain_1">
           <figure>
               <a href="/resource/highsm.13254/" tabindex="-1">
               <img alt="A sculpted bust of Kahlil Gibran rests atop a fountain in a parklike setting."
                   
                   src="/static/portals/free-to-use/public-domain/arab-americans/arab-americans-1.jpg"
                   
                    />
               </a>
           </figure>
           <div class="description">
           <div class="item-description">
           <h2><a href="/resource/highsm.13254/"><span>Kahlil Gibran, a Lebanese American poet and author. Memorial in Washington, D.C. Photo by Carol Highsmith, around 2000.</span></a></h2>
           </div>
           </div>
       </li>
       
       <li 
           id="featured_public_domain_2">
           <figure>
               <a href="/resource/afc1993001.afc1993001_195995_03/?sp=16" tabindex="-1">
               <img alt="Elderly woman plays the piano in her living room and sings from a piece of sheet music."
                   
                   src="/static/portals/free-to-use/public-domain/arab-americans/arab-americans-2.jpg"
                   
                    />
               </a>
           </figure>
           <div class="description">
           <div class="item-description">
           <h2><a href="/resource/afc1993001.afc1993001_195995_03/?sp=16"><span>Josephine Wehby Sharbel playing and singing the Lebanese national anthem. Photo by Brenda McCallum, 1982. Source: American Folklife Center, Ethnic Heritage and Language Schools in America Project collection
</span></a></h2>
           </div>
           </div>
       </li>
       
       <li 
           id="featured_public_domain_3">
           <figure>
               <a href="/resource/afc1993001.afc1993001_195995_03/?sp=4&amp;r=-0.546,-0.026,2.092,0.745,0" tabindex="-1">
               <img alt="A group of 32 children sits or stands for a group portrait outdoors. An adult stands on the right side. One person holds a U.S. flag above the group."
                   
